<main id="main" class="page page--prose">
  <h1 class="page-title">About Loktech</h1>

  <p><strong>Loktech</strong> is a one-stop repository of community AI-literacy resources —
  booklets, Jupyter notebooks and questionnaires — built <em>with</em> Marwari-speaking
  communities in the villages around Jodhpur, Rajasthan, not just <em>for</em> them.</p>

  <p>It is part of <strong>RAIL (Responsible Augmentation of Indigenous Languages)</strong>,
  a participatory framework for responsible AI. The aim is simple: help villagers
  understand everything from how a computer works to how AI works, see clearly both
  the benefits and the harms AI brings, and keep ownership of their own language and data.</p>

  <h2>What's inside</h2>
  <ul class="prose-list">
    <li><strong>Learn</strong> — a ground-up path from computers to AI.</li>
    <li><strong>Impact</strong> — the benefits and harms of AI, side by side.</li>
    <li><strong>News</strong> — critical and participatory AI updates from around the world.</li>
    <li><strong>Catalogue</strong> — all booklets, notebooks and questionnaires.</li>
    <li><strong>Original site</strong> — the first booklets, preserved exactly as written (in Marwari).</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="page-note">The new site is in English for now and will be translated to Marwari and
  Hindi. The original booklets are kept unchanged.</p>
</main>

